    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "I know that I can run a search in vim using `/`. I prefer having search highlighting turned on, but if I have a two splits with different files open, and I search for a term in one, they get highlighted as if I ran the same search or substitution in both. The same thing occurs with tabs as well.\r\nThis looks really wonky with certain plugins like `coc-explorer`:\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/95201/112572699-eff81580-8da7-11eb-80a6-6aa1442cf960.png)\r\n\r\nI wonder if a window or buffer local version of it could be implemented... I am not sure if this might imply window/buffer local searches as well, but maybe that would be a good thing? ",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
